Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 81
Edition:
Quote: <i>pack a sad</i> to be depressed; from builders' term for a warp; eg `Having dropped the ball with the line and the winning of the game in sight, Mick proved the night's party pooper, packing a sad all evening.'
